isk, log N_H(disk) = 20.7. If the FUV radiation\nfields are similar in disk and low halo, this suggests an enhanced\n(dust-catalyzed) H2 formation rate in higher-density, compressed clouds, which\ncould be detectable as high-latitude, sheetlike infrared cirrus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2005 19:50:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
