{"id":"quant-ph/0507248","submitter":"Dr Arun K. Pati","authors":"Arun K. Pati","title":"Quantum History cannot be Copied","comments":"Latex file, No figures, 9 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.physleta.2005.08.041","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We show that unitarity does not allow cloning of any two points in a ray.\nThis has implication for cloning of the geometric phase information in a\nquantum state. In particular, the quantum history which is encoded in the\ngeometric phase during cyclic evolution of a quantum system cannot be copied.\nWe also prove that the generalized geometric phase information cannot be copied\nby a unitary operation. We argue that our result also holds in the consistent\nhistory formulation of quantum mechanics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2005 15:37:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-26"}
